The Springs Council Chamber will on Friday be the venue for the Sector Parliament for Commercial Sex Workers.This is an initiative of the Gauteng Provincial Legislature aimed at creating a platform for meaningful engagement between public representatives and commercial sex workers . It seeks to destigmatise encourage engagements and recognise the work done to improve the understanding of the sex work environment a statement from the legislature said.It also allows for the sharing of much-needed knowledge about current challenges facing commercial sex workers including HIV prevention and empowerment opportunities concerning commercial sex workers rights access to health and well-being.- A review of government s stance on the involvement of commercial sex workers during policy review;- Plans to curb the influx of underage sex workers in the industry; and- Access to the justice system the battle for survival in the face of human trafficking abusive clients and police heavy-handedness. TMG Digital 